records.addlTxt:
Defendant Roger L. Hughey in court with attorney Gabriela A Leija.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction;  Huber privileges for work.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Complete parenting classes;
*  Possess no weapons;
*  Obtain GED;
*  Perform 20 hours of community service;
*  Maintain employment;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

If all conditions of probation (with the exception of the costs and surcharges) are completed, the Court will grant expungement.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
